Last Updated: 02/06/2017 



Executive Summary
Stephen Luczo has successfully turned around the fortunes of Seagate Technology during his tenure as CEO.  Luczo joined Seagate in 1993 as Senior Vice President of Corporate Development. He went on to serve as President and Chief Operating Officer of the Company’s predecessor, Seagate Technology, Inc. and, in July 1998, he w 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Luczo is the youngest of three sons of Thomas and Rose Luczo.
He attended public schools through high school and attended the University of Illinois at Champange-Urbana in 1976. 
Current Focus

Company Overview:  Founded in 1979, Seagate is the worldwide leader in hard disk drives and storage solutions.  From the videos, music and documents shared with friends and family on social networks, to server 
Key Challenges

Shift in Strategy:  The Company, which has been making products based on the needs of equipment manufacturers, is shifting its strategy to focus on technology buyers, includin 
Biographical Highlights

Luczo was born on February 28, 1957 in Chicago, Illinois.
He received a BA in Economics and Psychology from Stanford University (1976-1979) and holds an MBA from the Graduate School of Business at Stanford University (1982-1984 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Board of Directors, VMWare
Former Member, Board of Directors, Gadzoox Microsystems, Inc. 
 





